        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(data): add bounded data run evidence",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Add `crabbox data` as a thin wrapper over `crabbox run` for repo-owned data workflows with required bounded manifests.\n- Validate `crabbox.data-run.v1` manifests locally, reject unsafe proof fields, and write bounded summaries under `.crabbox/data-runs/`.\n- Add provider-neutral delegated artifact retrieval and W&B/CoreWeave single-file support for `--require-artifact` / `--download`, while keeping globs and unsupported delegated providers fail-closed.\n\n## Issues\nRefs https://github.com/openclaw/crabbox/issues/225\nRefs https://github.com/openclaw/crabbox/issues/227\nRefs https://github.com/openclaw/crabbox/issues/228\nRefs https://github.com/openclaw/crabbox/issues/229\nRefs https://github.com/openclaw/crabbox/issues/230\n\n## Test plan\n- `go test ./internal/cli ./internal/providers/wandb`\n- `go test ./...`\n- `scripts/check-docs.sh`\n\n## Live provider notes\n- Live W&B and Islo credentials were not present in the local environment, so this PR uses unit/local E2E coverage for delegated artifact retrieval and manifest validation. The new W&B path is covered with fake CoreWeave API tests, including required proof, local download, keep-on-failure, timing JSON, and oversized-file rejection before retrieval.\n\nMade with [Cursor](https://cursor.com)",
